"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-poland-to-send-troops-to-paris-olympics-amid-security-challenge\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Securing the Paris Olympics is stretching France's domestic forces.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1657026755271446e-16, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  PublishedMar 29, 2024, 02:35 AM  UpdatedMar 29, 2024, 10:49 PM  PARIS-France has asked its allies to send several thousand security personnel to help safeguard the Paris Olympics, officials said on March 28, underlining the strains caused by the sporting extravaganza.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 315, \"end\": 322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Several foreign nations are going to reinforce us in certain critical areas, such as dog-handling capabilities, where the needs are enormous,\\\" an official at the defence ministry said on condition of anonymity.\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_security\", \"score\": 0.9724234614927917, \"rank\": 0.02835856365678962, \"text\": \"defence\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_security\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_security\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official did not say how many foreign soldiers would be on French soil, but Polish Defence Minister Wladyslaw Kosiniak-Kamysz confirmed his country was joining \\\"an international coalition established by France\\\" for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9933359291538518, \"rank\": 0.004737370029633154, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Defence_minister\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.915173280912137e-14, \"text\": \"Defence Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Defence_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Defence_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A French interior ministry official said separately that in January, Paris had asked 46 allies to send 2,185 police reinforcements.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1043, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999108695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French interior ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 1110, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.656812650323275e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both officials played down the significance of the requests for foreign assistance.\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a classic move for host countries ahead of the organisation of major events,\\\" said the French interior ministry official.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999108695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French interior ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 2023 Rugby World Cup in France, European allies sent 160 police officers to help with security, the official added, with some of them visible to fans as they patrolled the streets.\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1420, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Securing the Paris Olympics is stretching France's domestic forces, however, and anattack on March 22 on a concert hall in Moscowthat killed more than 140 people, claimed by the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria (ISIS) militant group, underlined the stakes.\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1620, \"end\": 1626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1756, \"end\": 1769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 0.9999998292542077, \"rank\": 1.7074521243589947e-07, \"text\": \"Islamic State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 1773, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq\", \"score\": 0.8726782200325859, \"rank\": 0.1426667931598717, \"text\": \"Iraq\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iraq\"}, {\"begin\": 1782, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9883688761896193, \"rank\": 0.011767998860510023, \"text\": \"Syria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\"}, {\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0361670313455422e-28, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The terrorist threat is real, it's strong,\\\" French Prime Minister Gabriel Attal said on March 25, adding that two plots by suspected Islamic extremists had already been thwarted in 2024.\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 2022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1880, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Prime Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}, {\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\", \"score\": 0.9991858327172439, \"rank\": 0.0008148294453507712, \"text\": \"Islamic extremists\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Up to 45,000 French police and gendarmes are set to be deployed each day during the Olympics, while 18,000 troops are also expected to be mobilised, according to government figures.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7904875011064043e-34, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another 18,000-22,000 private security guards will be on the ground for the Games, which run from July 26 to Aug 11.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The request for foreign help was \\\"for the spectators' experience, to respond to the capacity challenge of the Games and to reinforce international cooperation\\\", said the French interior ministry official.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2495, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999108695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French interior ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany said in March that it would send an unspecified number of police officers to France for the Olympics, while French forces are set to travel to Germany when it holds the Euro 2024 football tournament in June and July.\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999764946098791, \"rank\": 1.9415030658551493e-05, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2616, \"end\": 2622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 2647, \"end\": 2653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9933359291538518, \"rank\": 0.004737370029633154, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 2682, \"end\": 2689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999764946098791, \"rank\": 1.9415030658551493e-05, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics have been attacked in the past - in 1972 in Munich and again in 1996 in Atlanta - with the thousands of athletes, huge crowds and live global television audience making it a target.\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2814, \"end\": 2820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.8926932512599886, \"rank\": 0.12020320126439832, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.404239588573195e-13, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French organisers have faced persistent questioning over their decision to hold the opening ceremony outside the athletics stadium for the first time.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2953, \"end\": 2959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9933359291538518, \"rank\": 0.004737370029633154, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes are insteadset to sail down the river Seinein a flotilla of boats in a made-for-TV extravaganza.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The choice has been resisted by some security officials because of the challenges for police.\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French security forces arescreening up to a million people before the Games,including athletes and people living close to key infrastructure, according to the interior ministry.\", \"from\": 3306, \"to\": 3483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3306, \"end\": 3312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9933359291538518, \"rank\": 0.004737370029633154, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France was placed on its highest terror alert on March 24 following the Moscow attack.AFP  Olympics 2024  France  Poland  Olympics  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 3557, \"end\": 3563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999488800326, \"rank\": 3.573389081289866e-08, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 3591, \"end\": 3597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9836431029528349, \"rank\": 0.00973088615514367, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbped